        Official Singles Chart on 9/7/2021

        9 July 2021 - 15 July 2021

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UKs biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        I was always a believer any style or music of any age deserves a chance of being a hit single, thats the whole point of music.         Sorry whats acr?

        Dan Love

        9th July 2021
        2
        Vote score

        ACR is Accelerated Chart Ratio, if a song is more than 3 years old essentially it's streams are halved, so for example instead of 600 Spotify streams counting for a sale, 1200 Spotify streams are required for a sale. A single moves onto ACR if it is

        a) more than 3 years old
        b) 10+ weeks old and declined for 3 consecutive weeks

        As MrDannyDoodah says, its due to the primary song being streamed (or downloaded) is the track from New Orders Best-Of album. EnglandNewOrder as a #1, but the current track is being treated as a new release.

        We occasionally get this with other tracks where the Serial Number or label on re-release has changed even though the song is exactly the same. As well as chart position, week numbers also get impacted by the same effect. Last Christmas is a good example of that, which for a long time did not seem to register its #2 status (when it was a Double A with Everything She Wants).
